    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL TANDEM AXLE FORWARD REAR DRIVE UNITS -
        DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The 140, 145, and 160 forward axle drive units of these tandem axles have single-reduction, thru-drive
                carriers. The drive gearing is made of a two-helical gear train and a hypoid ring gear and pinion. Bevel
                gears are used in the main differential and the interaxle differential (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401101">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401101" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg14/G1401101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Interaxle Differential</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. INPUT SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. OIL PUMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HELICAL GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. INTER-AXLE DIFFERENTIAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. OUTPUT SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. RING GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. DRIVE PINION</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">For service procedures on rear carriers, refer to CTS-5080 in the CTS-5000 Master
                    Service Manual</emph>.
            </para>
            <para>The inter-axle differential is located behind the upper helical gear on the input shaft. The forward
                side gear of the inter-axle differential is part of the upper helical gear hub and the thru-shaft is
                splined to the rear side gear of the inter-axle differential (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401101">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <para>The 140, 145 and 160 have different features:</para>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>140 Series: A 15-inch ring gear is riveted to the differential case. An oil pump and a driver
                        controlled main differential are not available. The inter-axle differential is serviced as an
                        assembly.
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>RT-34-140: GAWR 34,000 lbs.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>RT-40-140: GAWR 40,000 lbs.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>145 Series: A 15-inch ring gear uses nuts and bolts to fasten the gear to the differential
                        case. An optional pump and a driver controlled main differential are available. The inter-axle
                        differential is serviced as an assembly.
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>RT-34-145: GAWR 34,000 lbs.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>RT-40-145: GAWR 40,000 lbs.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>RT-44-145: GAWR 44,000 lbs.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>160 Series: An 18-inch ring gear uses nuts and bolts to fasten the gear to the differential
                        case. An optional oil pump and a driver controlled main differential are available. The
                        inter-axle differential can be repaired. A wider helical driven gear is used. There are two
                        notches on the inter-axle differential case.
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>RT-46-160: GAWR 46,000 lbs.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>RT-52-160: GAWR 52,000 lbs. (
                                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401102">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <figure id="f1401102" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg14/G1401102.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Notch on Interaxle Differential Case</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The following options are available for the 145 and the 160 series axles.</para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
